cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.GR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the reliability of wireless sensor networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the connectivity of random graphs, which is a fundamental property of graph theory and falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses the notion of a strongly typical set, which is a concept from information theory. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the reliability of sensor networks, which can be seen as a type of information network. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper also discusses random geometric graphs, which can be used to model sensor networks generated by random sensor node deployment. This falls under the scope of graphics as it involves visualizing geometric graphs.
